text: Vihti is a municipality in Uusimaa, Finland. It is about northwest of the capital city Helsinki. As of 30 September 2023, 28,866 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Espoo, Hyvinkää, Karkkila, Kirkkonummi, Lohja, Loppi, Nurmijärvi and Siuntio. It was founded in 1867. == Other websites == * Municipality of Vihti – Official website Category:Municipalities of Uusimaa Category:1867 establishments in Finland
